17/05/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The chairman of the Slovenian Parliament, Jelko Kacin, said in an interview with Nedjeljni Vjesnik that Slovenia is Croatia's "best friend" along the road to EU membership.
In the interview, published Sunday (16 May), Kacin said Slovenia wants to see all members of the former Yugoslav federation enter the EU.
Slovenia joined the Union on 1 May.
In other news, Croatian and Slovenian firefighting and civil defence units held a joint exercise Saturday in the Slovenian town of Ormoz.
It tested rescue capabilities during a simulated crisis involving the release of dangerous substances along border areas.
(STA - 16/05/04;
HINA - 15/05/04)
